        <div class="textbox">
            <h2>What can I do on this website?</h2>
            <p>
                This website is meant as a way to keep track of scientific papers, and how different papers are connected, for example if they have the same author,
                the same topic or something else. These connections are blue and it is possible to click on them to read about the connection in detail. It is also possible 
                to create your own connections between papers and add a description, so you can remember why you created the connection in the first place.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="textbox">
            <h2>The limitations of the website</h2>
            <p>
                This website is only a vertical slice of a much bigger program. The focus of our team was on creating connections between papers and creating teams.
                If we had more time, we would implement a way to add papers, display the papers and create connections between already added papers, if there are any.
                We would also add a search function for papers, as well as an easy way to move around the graph of papers on the front screen.
